      <summary>What can I drink during the fasting window?</summary>
      <div class="faq-answer"><p>During the fasting window, you can drink water, plain black coffee, unsweetened green tea, herbal tea, and sparkling water without added flavors or sweeteners. These beverages contain zero or negligible calories and will not break your fast. Avoid adding milk, cream, sugar, or artificial sweeteners to your drinks, as even small amounts of calories can trigger an insulin response and disrupt the fasting state. Some experts allow up to 50 calories during the fast, but for maximum autophagy and fat-burning benefits, sticking to zero-calorie beverages is recommended.</p></div>
